  "response": "Sure! Here are some classic old songs across various genres that have stood the test of time:\n\n1. **Rock and Roll:**\n   - \"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin (1971)\n   - \"Hotel California\" by Eagles (1976)\n   - \"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen (1975)\n\n2. **Pop:**\n   - \"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston (1992)\n   - \"Billie Jean\" by Michael Jackson (1982)\n   - \"Like a Prayer\" by Madonna (1989)\n\n3. **Country:**\n   - \"Jolene\" by Dolly Parton (1973)\n   - \"Take Me Home, Country Roads\" by John Denver (1971)\n   - \"Ring of Fire\" by Johnny Cash (1963)\n\n4. **Soul/R&B:**\n   - \"Respect\" by Aretha Franklin (1967)\n   - \"What\u2019s Going On\" by Marvin Gaye (1971)\n   - \"Ain\u2019t No Mountain High Enough\" by Marvin Gaye & Tammi Terrell (1967)\n\n5. **Classics:**\n   - \"Yesterday\" by The Beatles (1965)\n   - \"Bridge Over Troubled Water\" by Simon & Garfunkel (1970)\n   - \"Sound of Silence\" by Simon & Garfunkel (1965)\n\nThese songs are cherished by many and have made significant cultural impacts.",
